Mariel Hemingway has written two books about growing up in a family plagued by depression, addiction and suicide . 
  Her grandfather Ernest committed suicide just months before she was born in 1961  . 
  Her sister Margaux was a model and her mother was a drug addict . 
  Mariel says her parents would drink and fight and she was left to clean up . 
  She has written Out Came The Sun for adults and Invisible Girl for teens . 
 